The Registrar shall perform the duties assigned to the Registrar under this Act and such other duties as the Chief Registrar may direct, and in particular be responsible for—
* the acceptance, transmission, service and custody of documents in
* facilitating the enforcement of decisions of the Court;
* certifying that any order, direction or decision is an order, direction or
* the maintenance of the Register of the Court;
* causing to be kept records of the proceedings and minutes of the
* managing and supervising the staff of the Court;
* the day to day administration of the Court;
* managing the library of the Court;
* facilitating access to judgments and records of the Court;
* undertaking any other duties assigned by Chief Registrar.
